description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Senior Mental Health Practitioner ( RMN, OT, SW or equivalent)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Band:&lt;/strong&gt; Band 6 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Winchester Community Mental Health Team &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Avalon House, Winchester &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a talented and experienced nurse? Do you want a chance to make a real impact on patients, service users and their families? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If so, look no further! This is a rare opportunity for an enthusiastic and highly motivated individual to join our friendly team at Winchester. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Winchester Community Mental Health team is based at the city centre of Winchester. It is commutable distance to London by road (M3) and rail (direct to Waterloo). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a team who really cares about their staff members and making sure that they are well looked after and support them by offering regular supervision with the line manager, and providing continuous training and development opportunities. The team culture has a focus on staff wellbeing and support. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to have experience of working with adults with mental health needs and have an interest in working with service users in a community setting. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your main responsibilities are: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate care for patients with severe and enduring mental health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in the teams “shared care” rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to run a clinic and / or groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care coordinate care packages which require involvement of other agencies, as well as producing reports, completing audits, supervising staff and mentoring students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Able to use your own initiative and organise your time efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good working knowledge of CPA processes and safeguarding knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to identify issues and demonstrate ownership of change processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have excellent assessment and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Car driver and use of car within work hours is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For informal visits and discussions, please contact Liz White (Team Leader) or Mandy James (Team Manager) on 01962 826000.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
